<figureCitation box="[836,901,1939,1963]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 2" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1698,1721]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1084,1637]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,1084,1654]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 2. Female Apocephalus species, apex of abdomen. 1. Lateral. 2. Dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281917/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">
Fig. 
<number box="[889,901,1939,1963]" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
) are not visible in all specimens, depending on preservation.
</paragraph>
